ollege. This was the first appointment of a professor of music at any American university."},{"number":2,"category":"religion","header":"Quit Rhode Island pulpit for Oberlin in 1835","body":"He was ordained pastor of the Congregational Church in Woonsocket Rhode Island in December 1834. Eleven months later he resigned to take up the Oberlin music professorship, where he served almost five years."},{"number":3,"category":"social_reform","header":"Went to Kansas Territory for the anti-slavery cause","body":"In April 1857 he resigned his Bloomington Illinois pulpit to go to Kansas in aid of the anti-slavery cause in the Kansas Territory. He labored at his own expense in the ministry near Burlingame until 1861."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"First wife dead after sixteen months","body":"He married Louisa Perry of Stockbridge in April 1835; she died sixteen months later in August 1836, leaving an infant son. He remarried Catharine Gillett in 1838 and had eight children with her."}],"slug":"elihu-ingersoll-1804"},"X00607":{"id":"X00607","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1810},"death":{"year":1886},"tags":[],"sources":[],"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"HD1696","children_ids":["HD1886","HD1887","HD1888","HD1889","HD1890","HD1891"],"marriage_number":1,"date_year":1838,"date_month":8,"date_day":15,"location_city":"Lorain","location_state":"Ohio"}],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"parents":{},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Catherine Gillett","first_name":"Catherine","maiden_name":"Gillett","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"